@endnode
@node "AmigaMods" "Amiga"
@next "ReactionMods"
@prev "Support Modules"
@{JRIGHT} Section Head: @{"Aglet Support Modules" LINK "Support"}@{line}
 Next subsection: @{"Reaction modules" LINK "ReactionMods"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}@{B}Amiga Library Definition Modules@{UB}

_________________________________________________________________________

@{JLEFT}@{_LMARG_}

The SDK include files defining the types and constants used by the Amiga libraries are the model for the set of Modula-2 DEFINITION modules serving the same purpose. The current definitions files were derived from SDK v53.15, with about a dozen updated to that of SDK v53.20.


In many cases, multiple related *.h files have been combined into one *.def file.
Also, in some cases the C definitions have been converted to utilize the more expressive type system of M2, often by introducing appropriate SET types where int or unsigned have been used in C.
The IMPLEMENTATION module for these *.h file conversions is usually empty.


The AOS4 library interfaces are represented by one or more RECORD type definitions representing the interface jump table. These have usually been placed into a Modula-2 DEFINITION module named after the Amiga library, eg, "DEFINITION MODULE IntuitionInterfaces".


The IMPLEMENTATION module for these interface definitions auto-opens the library and interface on module initialization, and closes them on module termination. See more details in @{" Amiga Library Calls " LINK "ALIB"} and @{" Library Auto-Open " LINK "LibAutoOpen"}@{line}

@{"Amiga Lib Modules List" LINK "AmigaModsList"}@{line}

.
@endnode
