@node "TextIOHelper" "TextIOHelper"
@{settabs 35 65}
@{JRIGHT} Section Head: @{"Aglet Support Modules" LINK "Support"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}
@{B}TextIOHelper Module@{UB}

_________________________________________________________________________

@{JLEFT}@{_LMARG_}

I found myself repeatedly making the same logic errors in simply reading plain text files using the procedures in the ISO TextIO module directory.@{line}

TextIOHelper was written to make it easier to get it right. And it adds a couple of other fillips: skipping blank lines and using expandable strings to handle long lines.@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}
@{b}
____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________@{line}
|@{line}
| PROCEDURE ReadNextLine(cid:ChanId; VAR OneLine:ARRAY OF CHAR):ReadResults;@{line}
| PROCEDURE ReadNextNonBlankLine(cid:ChanId; VAR OneLine:ARRAY OF CHAR; VAR NumSkipped:CARDINAL):ReadResults;@{line}
|@{line}
| PROCEDURE dReadNextLine(cid:ChanId; VAR dOneLine:DynStr):ReadResults;@{line}
|      (* dOneLine must exist or .str be NIL *)@{line}
| PROCEDURE dReadNextNonBlankLine(cid:ChanId; VAR dOneLine:DynStr; VAR NumSkipped:CARDINAL):ReadResults;@{line}
|@{line}
|@{ub}(*@{line}@{b}
|@{ub}    ReadNextLine  - silently truncates any line that won't fit in the OneLine parameter@{line}@{b}
|@{ub}                  - never returns endOfLine. For empty line returns allRight with empty OneLine@{line}@{b}
|@{ub}                  - endOfInput is returned only on the call AFTER the one that returned the@{line}@{b}
|@{ub}                    last line allRight.@{line}@{b}
|@{line}
|@{ub}    dReadNextLine - reallocates dOneLine to be larger if necessary.@{line}@{b}
|@{ub}*)@{line}@{b}
|____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________@{line}
@{ub}
@endnode
@node "ExperimentalMods" "ExperimentalMods"
@tab 43
@next "Amiga_Specific"
@{JRIGHT} Section Head: @{"Aglet Support Modules" LINK "Support"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}
@{B}Aglet Experimental Mods@{UB}

_________________________________________________________________________

@{JLEFT}@{_LMARG_}

@{b}@{u}Amiga Specific@{uu}@{ub}@{line}
   IconSupport@{tab}For creating and updating Workbench icons.@{line}

@{B}@{u}GUI@{uu}@{UB}@{line}
  @{" SimpleGUI " LINK "SimpleGUI"}@{tab}Implemented as a layer above Reaction@{line}
