@endnode
@node "IDE_Tutorial" "IDE_Tutorial"
@{JRIGHT} Prev section: @{"Example Programs" LINK "M2_Examples"}@{line}
 Next section: @{"M2IDE" LINK "M2_IDE"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}
@{B}IDE Tutorial@{UB}

_________________________________________________________________________@{line}
@{JLEFT}@{_LMARG_}

This tutorial takes you through the steps in a coding task: adding a missing feature in a working program (in this case @{i}M2IDE @{ui} itself). It assumes that the project has already been created and used to build one or more earlier versions of the program. (see @{" Using IDE " LINK "IDE_Using"} below for setting up a new project)@{line}

The problem fixed in this tutorial is that @{i}M2IDE @{ui} has three windows, the Proj Window, the NameList Window, and the BuildPrefs Window, but on right-press the program menu did not appear when the BuildPrefs Window is active.@{line}

Evidently, I had neglected to attach the menustrip to that window.
In this tutorial, we will correct that using the IDE environment.@{line}

Start from the CLI with this command:@{line}
@{b}
      _____________________________________________________@{line}
     |@{line}
     | 4.Work:Aglet/M2-v3/Compiler/wrk> run m2ide m2ide@{line}
     |_____________________________________________________@{line}
@{ub}

A file "M2IDE.prj" does exist in this directory, so it is opened and read, displaying the two @{" starting windows " LINK "IDETut1.jpg/MAIN"} (as well as the logging window).@{line}

The Proj window on the right shows the shows the project specific files. The NameList window on the left starts off showing the Miscellaneous file list, into which in this case I had put two "library" support Definition module sources, so I can quickly refer them them while programming.@{line}

Using the cycle gadget in the NameList window, we can see the list of @{" Registered mods " LINK "IDETut2.jpg/MAIN"} which were read in from the *.prj file. These are essentially all the Amiga/Reaction/ISO/Aglet support modules that we assume to be a fixed context and do not want or need to edit or re-compile while we are working at this project.@{line}

Note that, at this point, the Proj window shows all its modules as up-to-date.@{line}

@{_HEADING_ "Deciding where to start"}

In this case the first programming change stems from the fact that the BuildPrefs window display is handled entirely within module M2IDEcomp, and that it uses module SimpleGUI, which monitors window, gadget, and menu events for it. The program commands are generated within M2IDEcomp, but passed onto module M2IDEmsg for processing.@{line}

We need to add a way to also pass on menu events from M2IDEcomp. Thus we will have to change a procedure declaration in the Definition module to include an menu support in the window.@{line}

So, a double click on the DEF column of the M2IDEcomp row in the Proj window gets @{" M2IDEcomp.def " LINK "IDETut3.jpg/MAIN"} opened into the editor.@{line}@{_LMARG_}

@{"Tutorial Next" LINK "IDE_Tut1"}




 
@endnode
@node "IDE_Tut1" "IDE_Tut1"
@{JRIGHT} Section head: @{"IDE Tutorial" LINK "IDE_Tutorial"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}
@{B}IDE Tutorial@{UB}, continued

_________________________________________________________________________@{line}
@{JLEFT}@{_LMARG_}

@{_HEADING_ "The Definition Module Edit"}

The procedure interface to be changed is that of GetPrefsWndoCmd(). An extra parameter must be added to return the menu EventInfo.@{line}

ie, this:@{line}
@{b}
      _________________________________________________________________________________@{line}
     |@{line}
     | PROCEDURE GetPrefsWndoCmd(VAR cmd:Commands; VAR args:DynStr):BOOLEAN;@{line}
     |        (* args must exist *)@{line}
     |_________________________________________________________________________________@{line}
@{ub}

is edited to this:@{line}
@{b}
      _________________________________________________________________________________@{line}
     |@{line}
     | PROCEDURE GetPrefsWndoCmd(VAR cmd:Commands; VAR args:DynStr; VAR ev:EvntInfo):BOOLEAN;@{line}
     |       (* args must exist *)@{line}
     |       (* if returns TRUE and NullCmd, ev will carry a Menu event *)@{line}
     |_________________________________________________________________________________@{line}
@{ub}  

Now with the DEF column selected in the M2IDEcomp row, hitting the COMP button in the Proj Window compiles the desired Definition file, giving this text in the logging window:@{line}
@{b}
      _________________________________________________________________________________@{line}
     |@{line}
     | Aglet Mod2@{line}
     | PROGDIR:Mod2  -rngchk -ovflchk -instrubuf 2500 -optlev 2 M2IDEcomp.DEF@{line}
     |@{line}
     | Mod2 v3.0 Compiler Alpha0 (29.5.2008)@{line}
     | Copyright (c) 2004 by Thomas Breeden@{line}
     | M2IDEcomp.DEF@{line}
     |  <- M2Lv3:SimpleGUI.SBM@{line}
     |@{line}
     |  -> M2IDEcomp.SBM@{line}
     |_________________________________________________________________________________@{line}
@{ub}

@{i}M2IDE @{ui}now has updated the @{" Proj window " LINK "IDETut4.jpg/MAIN"} to show that the modules dependent on M2IDEcomp.def need to be recompiled.@{line}
@endnode
@node "IDE_Tut2" "IDE_Tut2"
@{JRIGHT} Section head: @{"IDE Tutorial" LINK "IDE_Tutorial"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}
@{B}IDE Tutorial@{UB}, continued

_________________________________________________________________________@{line}
@{JLEFT}@{_LMARG_}

@{_HEADING_ "Attaching the Menu"}

File M2IDEcomp's window handling implementation code must be edited so that the program menu appears when the BuildPrefs window is active.@{line}

This is easy to do using these two procedure already existing in module M2IDEmenus :

@{b}
   ______________________________________________________________@{line}
   |@{line}
   | PROCEDURE ShareMenu(AccessoryWndo:Wndo);@{line}
   | PROCEDURE UnshareMenu(AccessoryWndo:Wndo);@{line}
   |_____________________________________________________________@{line}
@{ub} 

The main program window, handled by module M2IDEgui, creates and owns the menu structure, so all we have to do in M2IDEcomp is make sure it is attached to the BuildPrefs window when it is opened, and removed before it is closed.@{line}

Double click on the MOD column of the M2IDEcomp row in the Proj window to get @{" M2IDEcomp.mod " LINK "IDETut5.jpg/MAIN"} opened into the editor.@{line}

There is one place where the window is opened, that we just edit to this:@{line}
@{b}
   ______________________________________________________________@{line}
   |@{line}
   | OpenWndo(PrefsWndo, wPosition, "M2IDE Build Prefs");@{line}
   | IF PrefsWndo # NullWndo() THEN@{line}
   |    ShareMenu(ProfsWndo);@{line}
   |    RETURN TRUE;@{line}
   | ...@{line}
   |_____________________________________________________________@{line}
@{ub}

The unshare call needs to go before the CloseWndo() in the exported procedure M2IDEcomp.HideBuildSettingsWin().@{line}
@{b}
   ______________________________________________________________@{line}
   |@{line}
   | (*==============================*)@{line}
   |  PROCEDURE HideBuildSettingsWin;@{line}
   | (*==============================*)@{line}
   |@{line}
   | BEGIN@{line}
   |@{line}
   | IF IsWndoOpen(PrefsWndo) THEN@{line}
   |    UnshareMenu(PrefsWndo);@{line}
   |    CloseWndo(PrefsWndo);@{line}
   | END;@{line}
   |@{line}
   | END HideBuildSettingsWin;@{line}
   |_____________________________________________________________@{line}
@{ub}

Another place to put the unshare call is into the termination code of the module M2IDEcomp, in case the program closes down while the BuildPrefs window is open.@{line}
@{b}
   ______________________________________________________________@{line}
   |@{line}
   | FINALLY@{line}
   | ...@{line}
   | IF PrefsWndo # NullWndo() THEN@{line}
   |    IF IsWndoOpen(PrefsWndo) THEN@{line}
   |       UnshareMenu(PrefsWndo);@{line}
   |    END;@{line}
   |    DisposeWndo(PrefsWndo);@{line}
   | ...@{line}
   |_____________________________________________________________@{line}
@{ub}

 
@endnode
@node "IDE_Tut3" "IDE_Tut3"
@{JRIGHT} Section head: @{"IDE Tutorial" LINK "IDE_Tutorial"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}
@{B}IDE Tutorial@{UB}, continued

_________________________________________________________________________@{line}
@{JLEFT}@{_LMARG_}

@{_HEADING_ "Handling the Menu Event"}

In M2IDEcomp.GetPrefsWndoCmd(), events that SimpleGUI has been accumulating for the BuildPrefs window are being unqueued. The update needed here is simply to check for and return the EventInfo parameter in the case of a MenuEv.@{line}

Just add a check into the WHILE loop:@{line}
@{b}
   ______________________________________________________________@{line}
   |@{line}
   | WHILE GetWndoEvnt(PrefsWndo, ev) DO@{line}
   |@{line}
   |    ...@{line}
   |@{line}
   |    ELSIF ev.ev = MenuEv THEN@{line}
   |@{line}
   |       cmd := NullCmd;       (* but return TRUE *)@{line}
   |_____________________________________________________________@{line}
@{ub}

GetPrefsWndoCmd() is called by a procedure that acts as the main input loop for the program, M2IDEmsg.GetCmd(), defined as:.@{line}
@{b}
   ______________________________________________________________@{line}
   |@{line}
   | PROCEDURE GetCmd(wndo:Wndo; VAR cmd:Commands; VAR args:DynStr);@{line}
   |_____________________________________________________________@{line}
@{ub}

So, in that procedure within M2IDEmsg, we change the call to GetPrefsWndoCmd() to receive the EventInfo parameter and use a procedure, HandleMenuEvent, to change it into a program command (as is done with the other two windows):

@{b}
   ______________________________________________________________@{line}
   |@{line}
   | IF GetPrefsWndoCmd(cmd, args, ev) THEN@{line}
   |    IF (cmd = NullCmd) AND (ev.ev = MenuEv) THEN@{line}
   |       HandleMenuEvent(ev, done, cmd, args);@{line}
   |    ELSE@{line}
   |       done := cmd # NullCmd;@{line}
   |    END;@{line}
   | ...@{line}
   |_____________________________________________________________@{line}
@{ub}
@endnode
@node "IDE_Tut4" "IDE_Tut4"
@{JRIGHT} Section head: @{"IDE Tutorial" LINK "IDE_Tutorial"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}
@{B}IDE Tutorial@{UB}, continued

_________________________________________________________________________@{line}
@{JLEFT}@{_LMARG_}

@{_HEADING_ "Rebuilding the Program"}

The above should be the necessary edits.@{line}

Now, in the Proj window, selecting the MOD column in the row with M2IDE (the program module), and clickinkg on the UPDATE button does all the necessary recompiles.@{line}

The IDE compiles all the pending to-be-compiled Implementation modules successfully except for M2IDEcomp.mod. The Logger window shows @{" this " LINK "IDETut7.jpg/MAIN"}, and the
project window shows M2IDEcomp.mod is @{" still to be compiled " LINK "IDETut8.jpg/MAIN"}.@{line}

The IDE has sent a message to the editor and checking the editor window for M2IDEcomp.mod we see that it is @{" positioned at the error " LINK "IDETut9.jpg/MAIN"}, with the M2 error message in the window title bar.@{line}

Oops. The error is clear: a typo of "ProfsWndo" instead of "PrefsWindo". The NEXT button in the Proj windows does not find another error.@{line}

The BuildPrefs have been set up previously, and were read in with the *.prj file, so we should be able to complete the build immediately. Since there is only one module to be compiled, we can select M2IDEcomp MOD and click on the Proj window "+" button, which causes the IDE to first compile the selected Implementation module and then run @{i}Mod2Lnk @{ui} on the project. This is successful; the logger window shows @{" this " LINK "IDETut10.jpg/MAIN"}.@{line}

Evidently, the design of the inter-module calls of @{i}M2IDE @{ui} could use some attention, but these warnings have been investigated and the calls determined not to be a problem.@{line}

Now if we quit the running @{i}M2IDE @{ui} and restart it, the problem is fixed: when the BuildPrefs window is open and active, the program Menu still appears and is effective!
@endnode
@node "M2_IDE" "M2_IDE"
@tab 40
@{JRIGHT} Prev section: @{"IDE Tutorial" LINK "IDE_Tutorial"}@{line}
 Next section: @{"Release History" LINK "Version_History"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}@{B}Integrated Development Environment@{UB}

_________________________________________________________________________

@{JLEFT}@{_LMARG_}

M2IDE@{tab}@{" > " LINK "IDE"}

Using M2IDE@{tab}@{" > " LINK "IDE_Using"}


Project Window@{tab}@{" > " LINK "IDE_ProjWin"}

Name List Window@{tab}@{" > " LINK "IDE_NamListWin"}

Build Prefs Window@{tab}@{" > " LINK "IDE_CompPrefsWin"}

Logger Window@{tab}@{" > " LINK "IDE_LoggerWin"}


Project Menu@{tab}@{" > " LINK "IDE_ProjMenu"}

Settings Menu@{tab}@{" > " LINK "IDE_SettingsMenu"}

Tools Menu@{tab}@{" > " LINK "IDE_ToolsMenu"}


