@endnode
@node "IDE" "M2IDE"
@{JRIGHT} Section Head: @{"Integrated Development Env" LINK "M2_IDE"}@{line}
 Next subsection: @{"Using M2IDE" LINK "IDE_Using"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}
@{B}M2IDE@{UB}

_________________________________________________________________________@{_LMARG_}
@{line}@{JLEFT}

M2IDE is the first step toward an Integrated Development Environment for @{i}Aglet Modula-2 @{ui}. Though it currently lacks quite a lot of what one would want in an IDE, I think it still can make developing with Modula-2 easier and faster.@{line}

@{_HEADING_ "Requirements"}

M2IDE makes use of ARexx for communicating with the selected editor. RexxMast must have been
started and be working well.@{line}

The logger window utilizes the PIPE device. That device should be in your SYS:Devs/DOSDrivers directory.@{_LMARG_}@{line}

@{_HEADING_ "Features"}

> Analyzes all the directly and indirectly imported project modules for a program and determines the appropriate compile order for definition and implementation modules.


> Allows standard and other "library" modules to be excluded, as you normally don't want to change or re-compile these.


> Displays the set of project modules in a "point-and-click" window.


> Has "Compile" (and "Link") buttons to act on the selected module via a button click.


> Communicates with an editor (currently GoldEd, Annotate, CygnusEd, or TurboText) to automatically save any of the concerned
files before the compile and to move the editor's cursor to the error position of a compile error.


> Has an "Update" button to do a build on the selected module, ie automatically compile all (and only) the out of
date modules and their dependencies in the correct order to create the ready to be linked set of object modules.


> Provides a simple GUI to most of the compiler and pre-linker switches.
@{_LMARG_}


.
@endnode
@node "IDE_Using" "Using M2IDE"
@{JRIGHT} Section Head: @{"Integrated Development Env" LINK "M2_IDE"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}
@{B}Using IDE@{UB}

_________________________________________________________________________@{_LMARG_}
@{line}@{JLEFT}


@{_HEADING_ "Starting"}

The program template is:        "FILE,-EDITOR/K,-D=-d/S".@{line}

"FILE",@{_LRGDENT_} is the name of the the project (.PRJ) file. If no <File>.prj is found, a basic project will be created in the current directory with the program module assumed to be <File>.mod in the current directory also.@{line}

Note that M2IDE will never create a new .MOD or .DEF file, only find an existing one, so you must use the editor to create <file>.mod in the current directory (or other specified Source Dir) either before or after starting @{i}M2IDE @{ui}.@{line}
@{_SMLDENT_}

"-EDITOR"@{_LRGDENT_} specifies on startup the name of the editor interface program (plugin) eg, "PROGDIR:GedFront", or "PROGDIR:TtxFront". If none is given, "PROGDIR:EdtFront" will be used.@{_LMARG_}


@{_HEADING_ "Setting up a New Project"}

Any non-trivial program will broken up into multiple modules, each of which will need to be compiled (ie, not including stable support modules). These can be created with the editor as needed. Once they are imported into <File>.mod (or one of its dependencies) a Refresh will bring them into the project.@{line}

If you want to store these in different directories, e.g the implementations in subdirectory MOD/ and the definitions in subdirectory DEF/, the first thing you need to do upon creating the project is to go to the "Sources Path" selection in the Name List window and enter those directories (in this case "MOD" and then "DEF" in the list of paths searched for compilable sources. All the library and other established support modules from Aglet will have been automatically read into Registered Modules name list so the @{i}M2IDE @{ui} will not try to re-compile them.@{line}

The symbol files (.SBM) needed for compiling with IMPORTed module are searched for in the current directory, and in the assignment "M2LV3:", set up as a multi-assign as described in the installation instructions.@{line}

Finally, you may want to put some files into the Misc Files name list for quick access to reference and note files useful for the new project.@{line} 
@{_LMARG_}

@{_HEADING_ "Windows"}

@{" Project " LINK "IDE_ProjWin"},  @{" Name Lists " LINK "IDE_NamListWin"},  @{" M2IDELogger " LINK "IDE_LoggerWin"},  @{" Build Prefs " LINK "IDE_CompPrefsWin"}
@{_LMARG_}@{line}

@{_HEADING_ "Menu"}

@{" Project " LINK "IDE_ProjMenu"}, @{" Settings " LINK "IDE_SettingsMenu"}, @{" Tools " LINK "IDE_ToolsMenu"}
@{_LMARG_}


@{line}
@endnode
@node "IDE_ProjWin" "M2IDE Project Window"
@tab 23
@{JRIGHT} Section Head: @{"Integrated Development Env" LINK "M2_IDE"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}

@{" Project Window " LINK "ProjWin.jpg/MAIN"}

_________________________________________________________________________

@{JLEFT}@{_LMARG_}@{line}
@{B}Def/Mod List@{UB}

@{_SMLDENT_}

Double Clicking on one of the DEF or MOD column entries will send a message to the editor to open (or bring-to-front)
the corresponding source file.
@{_LMARG_}@{line}

@{B}Buttons@{UB}

@{_SMLDENT_}

Refresh  @{LINDENT 23}Re-check the file dates, and import dependencies, and re-calculate the compiles needed for the entire project.
@{_SMLDENT_}


Update   @{LINDENT 23}Compile, in appropriate sequence, all Definition and Implementation modules used or referenced by the selected module.@{_SMLDENT_}


Comp  @{LINDENT 23}Compile the selected module. If it is a Definition module, mark as "to-be-compiled" any modules dependent on this one.
@{_SMLDENT_}


Link  @{LINDENT 23}Link the root module (program).
@{_SMLDENT_}


"+"   @{LINDENT 23}Compile the selected module and then Link the root module (program).
@{_SMLDENT_}


Next  @{LINDENT 23}Look for an T:*.ERR file for the selected module, and if found, open the editor at the next error position indicated for the source file.
@{_LMARG_}@{line}

The buttons (except for "Refresh") require a currently selected DEF or MOD column entry.@{line}

The "Comp" and "Update" buttons automatically send a request to the editor to save of the source file(s) before compiling.


-
@endnode
@node "IDE_NamListWin" "M2IDE Name Lists"
@tab 35
@{JRIGHT} Section Head: @{"Integrated Development Env" LINK "M2_IDE"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}

@{" Name Lists Window " LINK "NLWin.jpg/MAIN"}

_________________________________________________________________________

@{JLEFT}@{_LMARG_}

@{B}Name Lists@{UB}
@{_SMLDENT_}

Sources Paths  @{LINDENT 35}List of paths (besides the project file directory) @{i}M2IDE @{ui} is to use in searching for DEFINITION and IMPLEMENTATION source files for the project.
@{_SMLDENT_}


LibSources Paths  @{LINDENT 35}<NYI>
@{_SMLDENT_}


Registered Mods   @{LINDENT 35}These modules are "registered" with this project as "library modules", ie, they are not brought into the Project Window and will not be compiled in building the project. If used in the project, their symbol and object files
are expected to be found in one of the directories of the multi-assign, "M2LV3:".
@{_SMLDENT_}


Root Mods   @{LINDENT 35}<Currently one root module is allowed, the program file.>
@{_SMLDENT_}


Misc Files  @{LINDENT 35}A list of files useful for the project, but not part of the project source. eg, documentation, notes, reminders, library DEFINITION modules. Double clicking on one of these names will open the file into the editor.
@{_LMARG_}@{line}

@{B}Buttons@{UB}
@{_SMLDENT_}

AppendNL @{LINDENT 35}Open a file of names, and merge them into the current project Name List
@{_SMLDENT_}


SaveNL   @{LINDENT 35}Save the current project Name List as a text file of names.
@{_LMARG_}@{line}

@{B}Supplied Name List Files@{UB}@{_SMLDENT_}

For use in the Registered Mods name list, the following text files of names are copied over during the installation:@{line}

System.nl@{tab}@{LINDENT 35}Compiler RTS modules@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}
Amiga.nl@{tab}@{LINDENT 35}Amiga library modules@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}
ISO.nl@{tab}@{LINDENT 35}ISO Standard Library modules@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}
Reaction.nl@{tab}@{LINDENT 35}Reaction Support@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}
Sysmod.nl@{tab}@{LINDENT 35}General programming support modules distributed with @{_AGM2_}@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}
Experimental.nl@{tab}@{LINDENT 35}In-progress modules distributed with @{_AGM2_}@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}

RegMods.nl@{tab}@{LINDENT 35}All the above name lists combined. The program automatically reads in this .nl file on creation of a new project. Generally, this is what you want in order not to edit or compile any
of the supplied support Modules, which remain stable across your own projects.

@{_LMARG_}

.
@endnode
@node "IDE_CompPrefsWin" "IDE_CompPrefsWin"
@{JRIGHT} Section Head: @{"Integrated Development Env" LINK "M2_IDE"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}

@{" Build Prefs Window " LINK "BuildPrefsWin.jpg/MAIN"}

_________________________________________________________________________

@{JLEFT}@{_LMARG_}

As of now, only a project-global compiler/linker settings configuration is available. In other words, if the
.prj file contains compiler settings, they will used for all modules in the project (unless changed by the user via the Build window).@{line}

To permanently associate the comp or link settings with the open project you need to hit the "Assign Proj (Comp)" or the "Assign Proj (Link)" buttons.@{line}

@{b}Note:@{ub} These buttons assign the setting to the project, but there is no project auto-saving; you still need to save the project itself for the assigned settings to be available next time you start the project up. You can do this from the File | Save menu item or from the @{"Project Needs Saving" LINK "NeedsSaving.jpg/MAIN"} button that appears at the bottom of the main project window.@{line}

The global environmental settings (see @{"IDE_SettingsMenu" LINK "IDE_SettingsMenu"}) are used if the project being opened has no associated project specific setting.@{line}

Currently, from the M2IDE GUI, there are only two settings for the "StaticLib" to be included in the link, "<none>" or "SDK:clib2/lib/libm.a".@{line} 
@endnode
@node "IDE_LoggerWin" "M2IDE Logger Window"
@{JRIGHT} Section Head: @{"Integrated Development Env" LINK "M2_IDE"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}

@{" M2IDE Logger Window " LINK "LoggerWin.jpg/MAIN"}

_________________________________________________________________________

@{JLEFT}@{_LMARG_}

All output from the compiles, links, and the Get Clients command appears in this window.@{line}
 
@endnode
@node "IDE_ProjMenu" "IDE_ProjMenu"
@{JRIGHT} Section Head: @{"Integrated Development Env" LINK "M2_IDE"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}
@{b}Project Menu@{ub}

_________________________________________________________________________

@{JLEFT}@{_LMARG_}@{line}

@{b}Open@{ub}@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}
Open an existing (or create a new) *.prj file. Only one can be open at a time.
@{_LMARG_}@{line}

@{b}Save@{ub}@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}
Save the currently open *.prj file.
@{_LMARG_}@{line}

@{b}About M2IDE@{ub}
@{_LMARG_}@{line}

@{b}Quit@{ub}@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}
Exit the program. If the *.prj file settings have changed, you will be asked if you want to save it. 
@{_LMARG_}@{line}
@endnode
@node "IDE_SettingsMenu" "IDE_SettingsMenu"
@{JRIGHT} Section Head: @{"Integrated Development Env" LINK "M2_IDE"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}
@{b}Settings Menu@{ub}

_________________________________________________________________________

@{JLEFT}@{_LMARG_}@{line}

@{b}Save Window Layout (ENVARC:)@{ub}@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}
The current positions and sizes of the M2IDE Project, Name Lists, and Build Settings windows will be saved in ENVARC. 
@{_LMARG_}@{line}

@{b}Save Comp Setting (ENVARC:)@{ub}@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}
Save the compiler setting into ENVARC. These will be used for all new projects and for any project that has not had an explicit set of compiler settings assigned to it via the Build Prefs window button.
@{_LMARG_}@{line}

@{b}Save Link Setting (ENVARC:)@{ub}@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}
As above, but for linker settings.
@{_LMARG_}@{line}

@{b}Make Icons?@{ub}@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}
If checked, then when the project file is saved, an icon will be created for it, with @{i}M2IDE @{ui} as its default tool.
@{_LMARG_}@{line}

@{b}Show Build Prefs ...@{ub}@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}
Open the Build Prefs window if it is not currently open or bring it to the front if it is.
@{_LMARG_}@{line}

@{b}Show Name Lists ...@{ub}@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}
As above, but for the Name Lists window.
@{_LMARG_}@{line}
@endnode
@node "IDE_ToolsMenu" "IDE_ToolsMenu"
@{JRIGHT} Section Head: @{"Integrated Development Env" LINK "M2_IDE"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}
@{b}Tools Menu@{ub}

_________________________________________________________________________

@{JLEFT}@{_LMARG_}@{line}

@{b}Get Clients@{ub}@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}
List all the client modules (in the Logger Window) of Proj window's currently selected DEF file.
@{_LMARG_}@{line}

@{b}Mark All Uncompiled@{ub}@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}
Mark all files listed in the Proj window as needing compilation. If you then follow up with a Update of the Program module, all the DEF and MOD files in the project will be compiled in the appropriate order.@{line}

Note that the mark-uncompiled action does not change the time-stamps on the files themselves, so a Refresh in the Proj window will undo this marking.
@{_LMARG_}@{line}

@{b}Make Build File@{ub}@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}
Write out a ADOS shell script which can be used to compile the whole project from scratch, in the appropriate order.
@{_LMARG_}@{line}
@endnode
@node "IDE_Other" "IDE_Other"
@tab 45
@{JRIGHT} Section Head: @{"Integrated Development Env" LINK "M2_IDE"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}
@{B}M2IDE Other Info@{UB}

_________________________________________________________________________@{_LMARG_}
@{line}@{JLEFT}     

@{B}Environment Variables@{UB}

@{LINDENT 3}

M2IDE/DefaultRegMods @{LINDENT 45}Name of a Names list file to use to load registered modules upon new project creation. Default is "PROGDIR:RegMods.NL"
@{LINDENT 3}@{line}

M2IDE/CompPrefs@{tab}<set by M2IDE>@{line}
M2IDE/LinkPrefs@{tab}<set by M2IDE>@{line}
M2IDE/PgmSettings@{tab}<set by M2IDE>@{line}
M2IDE/WinPos@{tab}<set by M2IDE>

@{PARD}

@{B}Installation@{UB}
@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}

Executables: M2IDE, EdtFront, M2IDELogger


Uses "PROGDIR:" for starting compiler, error lister, and pre-linker as well, so the above executables should be
installed in the same directory as Mod2, M2Err, and Mod2Lnk.
@{_LMARG_}@{line}
@{PARD}

@{B}KingCON@{UB}
@{_SMLDENT_}@{line}

If you run @{i}M2IDE @{ui} from the @{i}KingCON @{ui} shell it is a good idea to redirect output to NIL:, eg, "run M2IDE filename > NIL:".@{line}

Otherwise, @{i}KingCON @{ui} will block @{i}M2IDE @{ui} whenever a partial line is typed into the @{i}KingCON @{ui} window (even though @{i}M2IDE @{ui} redirects standard output).

.
@endnode
@node "Version_History" "Version_History"
@tab 31
@{JRIGHT} Prev section: @{"M2IDE" LINK "M2_IDE"}@{line}
@{JCENTER}
@{B}Release History@{UB}

_________________________________________________________________________

@{JLEFT}@{_LMARG_}

@{_HEADING_ "Apr 5, 2011"}
Compiler@{_ITM33_}- v3.1 Beta (13.2.2011)@{_ITEMEND_}

@{_ITM33_}Bugfixes:@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}@{u}TwoPower const Expressions@{uu} - "CARDINAL8 * TwoPowerConst -> CARDINAL32", were not generating correct code.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}@{u}Char Consts@{uu} - "CAP(c)", where c was a CONST CHAR was giving a compile error.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}@{u}Const params to std funcs@{uu} - "INT(801.0)", would malfunction on the second use.@{_ITEMEND_}

M2IDE@{_ITM33_}@{b}-@{ub} New editor "plug-in", AnnFront, integrates editor @{i}Annotate@{ui} into M2IDE.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}@{b}-@{ub} Status message now reports "ok" on successful compiles.@{_ITEMEND_}

Amiga Libs@{_ITM33_}- updated for release 53.20@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- DOS FileHandle and FileLock are now opaque types rather than ADDRESS.@{_ITEMEND_}                
@{_ITM33_}- Rasters is using AreaInfoPtr instead of ADDRESS for appropriate parameters.@{_ITEMEND_}                
@{_ITM33_}- GraphicsInterfaces VectorBuffer parameter for InitArea() changed from ARRAY OF POINT to ADDRESS. (It was not really an array of point).@{_ITEMEND_}                

Reaction@{_ITM33_}- updated for release 53.20@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- ReactionPrefs and UserInterfPrefs moved to directory "Reaction" from directory "Amiga".@{_ITEMEND_}                

ISO Mods@{_ITM33_}- RealStr v0.3 (10.10.2010)@{line}
     > Rounding is now implemented fairly correctly.@{line}
     > Changed code to compensate for a very infrequent glitch in compiler's TRUNC() code generation.@{line}
     > RealToFixed() is now working for reals bigger than approx 4294967300  (ie, 2^32-1)@{line}
     > WriteReal() and RealToFloat() now use the output space as ISO specifies.
@{_ITEMEND_}

Aglet Mods@{_ITM33_}- AmigaTimer v1.6 (13.12.2010)@{line}
     > Supporting new timer modes for "waituntil" and "entropy". Changed mode from a number to an enumeration type, TimerFlavors.@{line}
     > New procs GetEClock(), GetEClockFreq() and GetEntropyATimer()@{line}
     > A TimerHandle is no longer needed as a parameter for procs GetSysTime() and GetSysTOD()@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- StrMacros  v0.2 (3.4.2011)@{line}
     > missing comma between parameters in a macro call no long hang the program.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- SimpRexx1  v0.3  (13.3.2011)@{line}
     > Added automatic single quotes around Port name (necessary if port name does not happen to be all caps.@{_ITEMEND_}                
@{_ITM33_}- PipeIO v0.6  (16.2.2011)@{line}
     > Added ReadPipeLine() for more efficient buffered reading line by line.@{line}
     > Similarly, added dReadPipeLine() unlimited line lengths.@{line}
     > added a Timeout Exception feature.@{_ITEMEND_}                

Experimental@{_ITM33_}- OsRun  v0.3 (27.3.2011)@{line}
     > added Proc SpawnRedirect() to provide for specifying the standard in/out/err@{line}
     > added Proc BreakOffspring() to send ^C to all Spawned children.@{line}
     > added Procs WaitForStarted() and CheckForProcessRunning().@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- SimpleGraphics  v1.3 (16.2.2011)@{line}
     > Implemented BufferedScreens, at least enough for straightforward animations.@{line}
     > Methods ForeColor Get/Set moved from class GraphPlot up into parent class GraphRegion.@{line}
     > other bug fixes@{_ITEMEND_}                
@{_ITM33_}- Obj v1.1 (16.5.2010)@{line}
     > added func ooClassSameOrDescendent() so that you can test this, not just assert it.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_LMARG_}                


@{_HEADING_ "Feb 28, 2010"}
Compiler@{_ITM33_}- v3.1 Beta1 (22.2.2009)@{_ITEMEND_}

@{_ITM33_}Bugfixes:@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}@{u}Literal Set Expressions@{uu} - expressions like "3 IN BITSET{0,3)" were not generating correct code.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}@{u}Shift code@{uu} - SHIFT() to left for set sizes < 32 was resulting in erroneous relation expressions
and shift amount of 0 was generating incorrect code.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}@{u}Runtime checking@{uu} - wrong bits in XER register were being referenced@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}@{u}Subrange of CHAR@{uu} - compiler was rejecting subrange with literal chars like ['a'..'z']@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}@{u}Set of Boolean@{uu} - compiler was rejecting type def SET OF BOOLEAN@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}@{u}Comparison of Comparisons@{uu} - expressions like "(i = 5) = (j = 10)" were not handled correctly@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}@{u}Const Boolean Expressions@{uu} - const boolean expressions like "TRUE OR TRUE" and "DEBUG OR FALSE" were not being handled correctly.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}@{u}Real Expressions with Literals@{uu} - compiler rejected expressions like "12.343 - b", where b is REAL because the literal number was being treated as LONGREAL only.@{_ITEMEND_}

@{_ITM33_}Changes:@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}@{u}Default instruction buffer size@{uu} - Changed the default to 5000. Use the "-instrubuf" switch to compile with a different size@{_ITEMEND_}

M2IDE@{_ITM33_}@{b}-@{ub} new CLI startup switch, "-Editor"@{line}
Specifies on startup the name of the "...Front" editor interface program
eg, "PROGDIR:GedFront", or "PROGDIR:TtxFront". If none is given,
"PROGDIR:EdtFront" will be used as before.
The EditorInterfacePort still must be "M2IDEFRONT".@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- Removed LogWindowToFront() calls before each compile and each link.
These made it extremely hard to do anything else while compiling a big batch
of modules.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}@{b}-@{ub} Changes in editor interface program, GedFront, for Golded v8:@{line}
> Error display in editor had broken with switch from GoldEd v7 to v8.@{line}
> On startup of GoldEd, the "HIDE" switch was removed - does not work in GoldEd v8.@{_ITEMEND_}

System Mods@{_ITM33_}- Bugfix: The default input/output window opened when a program is started from Workbench
were not taking input from the keyboard. Now using CON: rather than RAW:
for this window.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}@{b}-@{ub} Module DebugIO (and thus also Debugging.DebugPause) now has a 60 second timeout.@{_ITEMEND_}

Aglet Mods@{_ITM33_}@{b}-@{ub} DateSupport module procs now interpret "AM" and "PM" in a time string.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- StrSubstitutes.DoSubst() now implements backslash as an "escape" char for
brackets. This also affects modules StrMacros and SimpleStrSubstitutes.@{_ITEMEND_}

Experimental@{_ITM33_}- New module for programatically starting independent CLI processes: OsRun.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- New module, DirUtilsDyn, using dynamic rather than static strings for file specs.@{_ITEMEND_} 

TestManager@{_ITM33_}@{b}-@{ub} Created a q+d program to manager automated runs of the tgM2 test generator program.
A dozen or so tgM2 driver files put together to create the beginning of an
effective compiler regression testing suite.

@{_ITEMEND_}        
@{_LMARG_}

@{_HEADING_ "Dec 16, 2009"}
Compiler@{_ITM33_}- v3.1 Beta1 (16.12.2009)@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- The compiler itself is now @{b}PPC native@{ub}, and is significantly faster!@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- The size limit on procedures is now probably large enough for any sane program.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- A bug which caused extremely excessive stack use was fixed. Now 40 or 50K should be enough for almost any compile.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- Some code generation errors were fixed.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- Fixed problem with Opaque pointers resolved within the IMPLEMENTATION module by imported pointer types.@{_ITEMEND_}        
@{_ITM33_}- Added compiler warning: OpenArrayCopyWarn.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- SDK 53.8+ now using the GNU assembler v2.18 vs. 2.14 in earlier SDKs. This required that some instructions be output slightly differently.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- Certain "recording" forms of FP instructions no longer generated, since Sam 440ep does not support them.@{_ITEMEND_}

(Pre)Linker@{_ITM33_}- @{i}Mod2Lnk @{ui} recognizes a @{b}"-stack" switch@{ub} and inserts the "$STACK:xxxx" cookie into executables.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- The .asm files no longer need be kept around. All (pre)linking information is in the object file now. Asm files are written to T:@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- Added the @{b}"-g" debug switch@{ub}, which causes both exported and non-exported symbols to be put into the Elf symbol table so that @{b}SymbolsRTS@{ub} can find them as well.@{_ITEMEND_}

M2IDE@{_ITM33_}- v0.3 (30.8.2009)@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- Option "@{b}Make Icons?@{ub}" added for the project file save.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- Fixed problem of GR on exit if M2IDE changed its current directory.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- Multiselect now supported for the "Misc Files" file requester.@{_ITEMEND_}

Amiga Modules@{_ITM33_}- Added Definition files for about @{b}25 more Amiga Libraries@{ub}, and all supplied Amiga definition files (over 150 of them) were brought up to the v53.13 SDK.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- The @{b}TextEditor gadget@{ub} is now working much better, as the Definition file now adjusts to a glitch in the SDK's .h file.@{_ITEMEND_}

Aglet Modules@{_ITM33_}- System module SymbolsRTS was introduced for better debugging of exception locations.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- CLI program arguments and Workbench ToolTypes are transparently (almost) unified when the ArgsSupport module is used to read startup arguments.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- Many improvements in the Simple... modules (SimpleGUI, SimpleScreens, SimpleMenus, SimpleGraphics, etc), but considering their overall incompleteness and fluidity I moved them into their own folder, "Experimental".@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- new modules: @{b}BigInt@{ub}, for 155 bit integers; @{b}IconSupport@{ub}, for writing out icons.@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_LMARG_}

@{_HEADING_ "Oct 26, 2008"}
M2IDE@{_ITM33_}- Fixed the intermittent, irritating, "broken PIPE" errors
that tended to show up in the IDE.@{_ITEMEND_}@{_LMARG_}

@{_HEADING_ "Aug 10, 2008"}
Compiler@{_ITM33_}- v3.0 Beta0 (3.8.2008)@{_ITEMEND_}

Documentation@{_ITM33_}- Expanded, corrected, and supplied as a PDF file as well as AmigaGuide.@{_ITEMEND_}

M2IDE@{_ITM33_}- Usability improvements in GUI.@{_ITEMEND_}

Aglet Modules@{_ITM33_}- small improvements in SimpleGUI and SimpleImageHandler modules@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- RTFWrite supports many more RTF constructs@{_ITEMEND_}
@{_ITM33_}- DynStr2B: new procedures dAddQuotes(), dRemoveQuotes().@{_ITEMEND_}@{_LMARG_}

@{_HEADING_ "July 5, 2008"}
- first one: v3.0 Alpha0 (22.6.2008)@{line}
@{_LMARG_}

@endnode
